==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nappe
<hw>Nappe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>nappe</ets>
cloth, sheet. See <er>Napery</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>Sheet;
surface; all that portion of a surface that is continuous in such a way
that it is possible to pass from any one point of the portion to any
other point of the portion without leaving the surface. Thus, some
hyperboloids have one <ex>nappe</ex>, and some have two.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nappiness</ent>⟦br⟧
